comment: Weaker version of ~ unxpwdom where a function is required only to be cancellative, not an injection. ` D ` and ` B ` are to be thought of as "large" "horizonal" sets, the others as "small". Because the operator is row-wise injective, but the whole row cannot inject into ` A ` , each row must hit an element of ` B ` ; by column injectivity, each row can be identified in at least one way by the ` B ` element that it hits and the column in which it is hit. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 8-Jul-2015.) _MOVABLE_
